The paper discusses a framework for deep learning architectural research, which involves optimization algorithms, meta-heuristics, and reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the framework is designed for image recognition tasks, which could place it in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of distributed computing could also suggest a potential fit in the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
